(2.1 MARKET REQUIREMENTS ) s
5 759 M
(At the March 1998 meeting, WG21 heard reports and discussion regarding the uses of C++) s
5 748 M
(in embedded, real-time, and high-performance projects.  Some of these projects have been) s
5 737 M
(migrating from C to C++, and have concerns for C++ performance issues.  The intent of) s
5 726 M
(the TR is to address these performance issues.) s
5 704 M
(2.2 ACHIEVEMENTS) s
5 682 M
(WG21 has developed internal procedures for receiving, logging, and addressing) s
5 671 M
(Defect Reports, consistent with JTC1 and SC22 directives.  Some new features:) s
5 660 M
(the moderators of the newsgroup comp.std.c++ play a role in the initial DR processing,) s
5 649 M
(and the WG21 web page provides reasonably current DR status information.) s
5 627 M
